In a speech, President Biden reflects on the state of the US economy after six months in office. He highlights the significant growth in job creation, with over 3 million new jobs added since he took office, and the highest economic growth rate in nearly 40 years. The President dismisses predictions of a depression or the end of capitalism, stating that capitalism is alive and well. He emphasizes the importance of getting the pandemic under control and urges Americans to get vaccinated. The President addresses concerns about inflation, stating that most price increases are temporary and due to global supply chain challenges. He emphasizes the need for investments in infrastructure and social programs to create jobs, raise wages, and keep prices affordable in the long term. The President also calls on Facebook to address misinformation about the COVID-19 vaccine. He concludes by expressing optimism about the future and the potential of the American economy.